            <div>
                <head>About the edition</head>
                <p>The sources on this portal have been published as part of the <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/en/home/">
                        <hi rend="u">Collection of Swiss Law Sources</hi></ref>. Financed by the Gemeinnützige Fonds des Kantons Zürich as well as contributions from the cities of Zurich and Winterthur, six editors have examined the sources from the cities of Zurich and Winterthur, the bailiwick (Landvogtei) of Greifensee as well as the bailiwicks (Obervogteien) in the vicinity of the city of Zürich. They have selected, transcribed and commented around 900 central pieces from several archives and libraries. Ranging from 1180 to 1798, the presented texts follow the principles of the <ref target="https://tei-c.org/">
                        <hi rend="u">Text Encoding Initiative (TEI)</hi></ref>. Thanks to the marking of persons, places and organizations in the transcribed source texts as well as linking them to the databases of the Collection of Swiss Law Sources, the online edition of Zürich’s legal sources is embedded in a whole digital network of research landscapes. The bibliographic information refers to the <ref target="https://www.nb.admin.ch/snl/en/home/research/bibliographies/bsh.html">
                        <hi rend="u">Bibliography of Swiss History</hi></ref>.</p>
                <p>The portal was built for the <ref target="https://www.zh.ch/de/direktion-der-justiz-und-des-innern/staatsarchiv.html">
                        <hi rend="u">Staatsarchiv des Kantons Zürich</hi>
                    </ref> by <ref target="https://jinntec.de/de/">
                        <hi rend="u">Jinntec GmbH</hi>
                    </ref> (technical realization) and <ref target="https://www.k-r.ch/">
                        <hi rend="u">Kränzle &amp; Ritter</hi>
                    </ref> (coordination). All parts of the publication are open source and available on <ref target="https://github.com/stazh/erqzh-data">
                        <hi rend="u">GitHub</hi></ref>. They can be reused according to the Creative Commons license <ref target="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/">
                        <hi rend="u">CC BY-NC-SA</hi>
                    </ref>. Photos are available for download as PDFs from the <ref target="https://suche.staatsarchiv.djiktzh.ch/suchinfo.aspx">
                        <hi rend="u">Archivkatalog</hi>
                    </ref>
                    <hi rend="u"> des Staatsarchivs Zürich</hi>. The edition follows the <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/wiki/Transkriptionsrichtlinien">
                        <hi rend="u">guidelines</hi>
                    </ref> of the <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/en/home/">
                        <hi rend="u">Law Sources Foundation of the Swiss Lawyers Society</hi>
                    </ref>.</p>
                <p>Several previous volumes have been published in print by the Collection of Swiss Law Sources and are now available online: Offnungen und Hofrechte von <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/online/ZH_AF_I_1/index.html#p_III">
                        <hi rend="u">Adlikon bis Bertschikon</hi>
                    </ref> und von <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/online/ZH_AF_I_2/index.html#p_III">
                        <hi rend="u">Binzikon bis Dürnten</hi>
                    </ref> (1910, 1915), <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/online/ZH_NF_I_1_1/index.html#p_III">
                        <hi rend="u">Zürcher Richtebrief</hi>
                    </ref> (2011) and <ref target="https://www.ssrq-sds-fds.ch/online/ZH_NF_II_1/index.html#p_III">
                        <hi rend="u">Rechtsquellen des Neuamts</hi>
                    </ref> (1996).</p>
                <p>After the completion of this project in 2022, more central sources will be published on the platform <ref target="https://qzh.sources-online.org/index.html">
                        <hi rend="u">Quellen zur Zürcher Geschichte (QZH)</hi>
                    </ref>, which is open for other projects and cooperation partners.</p>
            </div>
